metadata.name: SQUARE GAMES #111
metadata.description:
Quite frankely: a lot of squares

An exploration of recursion
featuring very vibrant color combinations
Interactive

4 recursion depths
16 color palettes
4 expansion states
4 fill probabilities 
4 ghost probabilities 

Press 's' to save a high res image
Click and move mouse to explore
Press 'space' to return to original position
Press 'b' to change color of white cube
Press ‚f‘ for fullscreen
Press 'p‘ to toggle pixel perfect rendering

metadata.name: The Bless of The Dawn #3
metadata.description:
This piece was interpreting the thought of perceiving dawn time as a blessed moment. Where the wonders might happen, evoking the ones who might be chosen to receive the enlightenment as their gift. The visual was inspired by the natural phenomenon called aurora borealis.

Take your time to enjoy the animation in live mode.

Press ’s’ on the live mode to save the screen capture.

Made using Hydra (https://hydra.ojack.xyz/)

metadata.name: Fingerprint #9
metadata.description:
Have you ever stopped to think that at the tip of your finger, there is a generative art, directly from your genetic code. this algorithm is inspired by this vision, the grid arrangement is formed by curves and rotations left in a trail of pixels, the trail of pixels is where the magic of this piece is, with the displacement of the grid in the form of a pendulum it creates ellipticals constructions  in modular functions. 

fx(hash) / Hydra / Marcelo Moura / 2022 / CC0 /

"Fingerprint"

metadata.name: Everyone needs more Liquidity #100
metadata.description:
Who doesn't?

This piece explores the dynamics of particle physics and liquid in an unbound system. In it, I set up a small space in which a particle system can play, bouncing off obstacles, creating rivers and falls, and responding to various physical constraints.

It is created using a webgl pipeline consisting of, primarily, a GPGPU particle system consisting of 16k particles in motion in real-time. The physics simulation is made possible using a compute shader (not really compute, given webgl, but you get the idea) which records the particles' position, velocity, age, and data to a texture for use by the point program. Each particle is rendered as a semi-transparent radial gradient, adding up to a distance field that is used to render the liquid.

metadata.name: AutomataPunk, The Masquerader #180
metadata.description:
A playful spin on PFPs, and the prevalence of them on social media, especially among the NFT community.
The characters are procedurally generated, and then colored and texturized using 1D Cellular Automata.
Masqueraders hide their rarity scores. The cutest or most unusual one will be the most popular.
Their dimensions are always a multiple of 360.

Controls:
- Press 's' to save a PNG file.
- Press 't' to toggle, for a larger and higher resolution version that once complete can be saved as a 3600x3600 PNG by pressing 's'. In this mode, the Masquerader may become much larger than your screen. Wait for its render to complete before saving it. Toggle back to the regular size by pressing 't' again.

License:
See included LICENSE.md

Credits:
Made in p5js
